#: ../../../release_details/9.4/fix-windowedsinc-scaling-error.md:1
msgid "Fix scaling error in vtkWindowedSincPolyDataFilter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/fix-windowedsinc-scaling-error.md:3
msgid ""
"The filter used Hamming window function for low-pass filtering, which "
"resulted in slight change (up to 1%) in the overall size of the smoothed "
"output (either larger or smaller)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/fix-windowedsinc-scaling-error.md:6
msgid ""
"Added the option to use Nuttall, Blackman, or Hanning window function that "
"does not suffer from this error, and changed the default to Nuttall, as it "
"consistently performed better (accurate smoothing with less iterations) than "
"all the others."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/fix-windowedsinc-scaling-error.md:9
msgid ""
"See more details in this discussion: https://discourse.vtk.org/t/slight-"
"offset-in-vtkwindowedsincpolydatafilter-if-normalization-is-enabled/7676"
msgstr ""
